        "Abstract": "We introduce Claire, a new French dialogue dataset collected from social media. Claire contains 10k conversations between two speakers, with an average of 10 turns per conversation. The dataset is designed to facilitate research on dialogue generation, language modeling, and sentiment analysis. We provide a detailed analysis of the dataset, including its size, diversity, and quality. We also present baseline results on several dialogue generation tasks, demonstrating the potential of Claire for advancing research in this area."
